CI check script: fails if any member crate's `Cargo.toml` omits `[lints]\nworkspace = true`, which is required for the workspace-level `[workspace.lints]` restriction table to apply to that crate. A crate lacking this opt-in silently gets zero lint enforcement, so this script is the only thing that catches that.

Enumerates manifests via `git ls-files -z --cached --others --exclude-standard -- 'Cargo.toml' '*/Cargo.toml'`, not a filesystem walk — mirrors the approach in `no_allow_check.sh` so results are a pure function of git state and don't race a concurrent `target/` writer. Skips any manifest without a `[package]` table (the virtual workspace root, or non-package manifests).

For each real crate manifest, uses an `awk` state machine to check specifically inside the `[lints]` table (entering on `^\[lints\]`, exiting on any other `^\[`) for a `workspace = true` line — deliberately avoids false positives from `workspace = true` appearing under `[workspace]` or elsewhere. `set -euo pipefail` is active; the manifest loop uses `${manifests[@]+"${manifests[@]}"}` to tolerate an empty array under `nounset`.

Invariant: exits nonzero (accumulates `FAIL=1`, doesn't short-circuit) if any qualifying crate manifest fails the check, printing one `FAIL:` line per offending manifest to stderr. Takes an optional root dir arg (default `.`); errors out if that path isn't inside a git work tree.